  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other crimes) to make it appear legitimate. \n\nMost jurisdictions have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering. For example:\n\n- In the **United States**, the **Bank Secrecy Act** and the **Patriot Act** are key pieces of legislation that criminalize money laundering.\n- In the **European Union**, the **Anti-Money Laundering Directive** (AMLD) provides a framework for member states to combat this crime.\n- Globally, organizations like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** set international standards to prevent money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include heavy fines, asset confiscation, and imprisonment. If you suspect or encounter money laundering, it is important to report it to the appropriate authorities.",
